Package org.anchoranalysis.feature.calculate.cache

Interface ResettableCalculation

All Known Implementing Classes:
CalculateDeriveMarkCollectionInput, CalculateDeriveMarkInput, CalculateDeriveObjectInput, CalculateDeriveSingleMemoFromPair, CalculateDilation, CalculateDilationMap, CalculateEllipseLeastSquares, CalculateEllipsoidLeastSquares, CalculateErosion, CalculateErosionMap, CalculateHistogram, CalculateHistogramMasked, CalculateIncrementalOperationMap, CalculateInputFromDelegate, CalculateInputFromDelegateOption, CalculateInputFromPair, CalculateIntersecting, CalculateNumberVoxels, CalculateObjectMask, CalculateOverlap, CalculateOverlapMask, CalculateOverlapMIP, CalculateOverlapMIPBase, CalculateOverlapMIPRatio, CalculatePointsFromOutline, CalculateShellObjectMask, FeatureCalculation, FeatureCalculationMap
public interface ResettableCalculation
A calculation that be invalidated (resetted), removing any existing cached value.

All resettable calculations must have a hashCode and equals implementation that checks that relevant parameters are equal. They will be used in sets

Author:
Owen Feehan

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void invalidate()
    Resets the cached-calculation, so the next call to doOperationWithParams() is guaranteed to calculation the operation, and store the value in the cache.
